# Vimtutor

This lesson is intentionally simple: start the built-in interactive tutorial
and follow it directly in the terminal.

`vimtutor` is the fastest way to build real editing muscle memory for modal
navigation, insert/normal mode switching, deletion, yank/paste, and search.

> **Performance note for this lab VM:** prefer `vi` for day-to-day editing in
> this browser environment. `vim` is available, and `vimtutor` is included for
> training.

## Start the Interactive Tutorial

Run:

```bash
vimtutor
```

Spend at least 10-15 minutes going through the guided steps.

If your terminal session cannot stay in full-screen interactive mode, you can
still verify the tool is installed with:

```bash
vimtutor -h
```

